<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocchino" authorityYear="1964" box="[181,325,1174,1198]" class="Osteichthyes (awaiting allocation)" family="Osteichthyes (awaiting allocation)" genus="Propygidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osteichthyes (awaiting allocation)" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,325,1174,1198]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Propygidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and pygidium densely punctate, punctation of pygidium becoming finer and sparser apically; pygidium slightly depressed laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,310,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Prosternum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[323,401,1271,1294]" captionStart="Figs 34–35" captionStartId="10.[151,188,966,985]" captionTargetBox="[246,1337,201,933]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[233,1355,189,958]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 34–35. Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 34 – habitus, dorsal view; 35 – prosternum, meso- and metaventrite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879860/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Prosternal process strongly compressed, keel-like, with fine scattered punctures; marginal prosternal stria present, terminating in large prosternal foveae; carinal prosternal striae divergent apically, terminating in prosternal foveae; lateral prosternal striae carinate, apically joining carinal striae at two-thirds point.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,326,1463,1487]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Mesoventrite</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[345,427,1463,1486]" captionStart="Figs 34–35" captionStartId="10.[151,188,966,985]" captionTargetBox="[246,1337,201,933]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[233,1355,189,958]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 34–35. Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 34 – habitus, dorsal view; 35 – prosternum, meso- and metaventrite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879860/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) approximately four times as wide as long, with scattered microscopic punctuation; marginal mesoventral stria complete, slightly carinate; meso-metaventral stria complete, undulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,319,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Metaventrite</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[332,409,1591,1614]" captionStart="Figs 34–35" captionStartId="10.[151,188,966,985]" captionTargetBox="[246,1337,201,933]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[233,1355,189,958]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 34–35. Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 34 – habitus, dorsal view; 35 – prosternum, meso- and metaventrite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879860/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Disc of metaventrite with sparse microscopic punctation, along apical margin double row of larger punctures present; lateral metaventral stria almost complete, slightly carinate, stopping short of metacoxa. Lateral disc of metaventrite with three rows of large deep punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,294,1782,1806]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,286,1782,1806]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
First visible abdominal ventrite slightly depressed on basal third, almost completely striate laterally, disc along margins with larger punctures, medially only with sparse microscopic punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,761,1047,2062]" lastBlockId="10.[828,1437,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,240,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Legs.</emphasis>
Protibia dilated, on outer margin with 4–5 low teeth, each topped by short amber denticle, outer row of setae regular, protarsal groove shallow, protibial stria complete and carinate, median row of setae very short. Protibial spur short, growing out from apical protibial margin; outer part of posterior surface of protibia rugulose-lacunose; median part of posterior surface glabrous; posterior protibial stria complete, with microscopic setae; setae of inner protibial margin double, dense and regular. Mesotibia slightly dilated, on outer margin with six prominent denticles, outer row of setae sparse; median row of setae microscopic and scattered. Posterior mesotibial stria complete; protibial spur conspicuous. Anterior mesotibial stria complete; a single inner row of setae. Metatibia slightly dilated, on outer margin with seven denticles progressively increasing in length apically; metatibia otherwise similar to mesotibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[858,1031,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1329,1399,1422]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Figs 36–37</figureCitation>
) strongly sclerotized, separated medially, extreme apices with tuft of microscopic setae. Tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1264,1463,1486]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) apically almost straight, not arcuate as in preceding species; sternite VIII and tergite VIII not fused laterally (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1310,1527,1550]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Tergite W (
<figureCitation box="[836,916,1559,1582]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) apically inwardly arcuate; tergite IW (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1429,1559,1582]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) somewhat more parallel-sided than in preceding species. Spiculum gastrale (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1178,1623,1646]" captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Figs 41–42</figureCitation>
) dilated on both ends, its apex (I ‘head’) strongly sclerotized. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 36–44" captionStartId="11.[150,187,1306,1325]" captionTargetBox="[289,1302,188,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[285,1302,159,1297]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36–44. Male genitalia of Euspilotus (Platysaprinus) ferreri sp. nov. 36 – VIII sternite and tergite, ventral view; 37 – ditto, dorsal view; 38 – ditto, lateral view; 39 – IW and W tergites, dorsal view; 40 – ditto, lateral view; 41 – IW sternite (spiculum gastrale), ventral view; 42 – ditto, lateral view; 43 – aedeagus, dorsal view; 44 – ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3879862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3879862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Figs 43–44</figureCitation>
) with slightly larger phallobase than with preceding species; ratio phallobase: parameres 1.0: 2.5; otherwise similar to preceding species, strongly curved from lateral view, apex not as pointed as with preceding species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="313" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[828,1437,1047,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,1077,1815,1838]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from 
<emphasis box="[1224,1240,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">E</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1890" box="[1255,1408,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Saprinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latimanus" subGenus="Platysaprinus">
(
<emphasis box="[1263,1279,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1303,1408,1815,1838]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">latimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of costate first dorsal elytral stria as well as by the non-costate lateral pygidial margins. Differs from 
<emphasis box="[828,844,1913,1936]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">E</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bickhardt" authorityYear="1910" box="[861,1076,1911,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Saprinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecophilus" subGenus="Platysaprinus">
(
<emphasis box="[870,886,1913,1936]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[912,1076,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">myrmecophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the impunctate basal third to half of the elytra, and from 
<emphasis box="[1118,1134,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">E</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lackner &amp; Arriagada &amp; AƶUR &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; AƶUR, 2020" authorityName="Lackner &amp; Arriagada &amp; AƶUR &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; AƶUR" authorityYear="2020" box="[1147,1321,1943,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Euspilotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vazdemelloi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Platysaprinus">
(
<emphasis box="[1156,1172,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1194,1321,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">vazdemelloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1328,1410,1943,1966]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the broadly-oval body and basally non-abbreviated dorsal elytral striae 3–4 (abbreviated in case of 
<emphasis box="[1240,1256,2009,2032]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">E</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lackner &amp; Arriagada &amp; AƶUR &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; AƶUR, 2020" authorityName="Lackner &amp; Arriagada &amp; AƶUR &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; RıAǤAĐA &amp; AƶUR" authorityYear="2020" box="[1267,1436,2007,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Euspilotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vazdemelloi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Platysaprinus">
(
<emphasis box="[1275,1291,2009,2032]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1311,1436,2007,2030]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="313">vazdemelloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[828,913,2039,2062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="313" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
)).
